You can use the cluster manager task throttling feature by calling the update cluster settings API in OpenSearch, you can set throttling limits for each task type in the cluster_manager.throttling.thresholds object, here is an example:
PUT _cluster/settings
{
  "persistent": {
    "cluster_manager.throttling.thresholds" : {
      "put-mapping" : {
          "value" : 1000
      }
    }
  }
}
you can see that this example set throttling limits to 1000 for the put-mapping task, if the number of put-mapping tasks exceeds 1000, the cluster manager will reject the incoming put-mapping tasks.

You can use the search backpressure feature by calling the update cluster settings API in OpenSearch, there are so many settings for search backpressure, here is an example that set search_backpressure.mode to enforced so that OpenSearch can cancel search requests which have breached the resource limits: 
PUT _cluster/settings
{
  "persistent": {
    "search_backpressure.mode" : "enforced"
  }
}

You can update the mapping of your index, set fielddata to true for the text field, like this:
PUT test_index/_mapping
{
  "properties": {
      "message":{
        "type":"text",
        "fielddata":true
      }
    }
}

There are many circuit breaker settings in OpenSearch, you can set them by using update cluster settings API, like this:
PUT _cluster/settings
{
  "persistent": {
      "*indices.breaker.total.limit*": "70%"
    }
}

